 THE PILOT WAS LANDING ON A SAND BAR IN CROSSWIND WEATHER CONDITIONS 
WHEN THE AIRCRAFT BOUNCED ON TOUCHDOWN, WEATHER VANED INTO THE WIND 
AND THE LEFT MAIN LANDING GEAR IMPACTED SOFT SAND.  THE LEFT WHEEL DUG 
INTO THE SAND, THE AIRCRAFT GROUND LOOPED, AND THE LEFT LANDING GEAR STRUT 
COLLAPSED. 
 THE PILOT'S FAILURE TO MAINTAIN DIRECTIONAL CONTROL DURING LANDING 
FLARE/TOUCHDOWN.  A FACTOR RELATING TO THE ACCIDENT WAS THE CROSSWIND 
WEATHER CONDITION. 
